Subject: [PATCH] Fix translation (multi-rule) + add 5 themed PVE campaigns +
 ticket button
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Translation:
- Migrate config['translation'] (singleton) -> config['translations'] (list)
- /translationconfig now ADDS or UPDATES a rule instead of overwriting
- Multiple rules can fire on the same message (enables bidirectional A<->B)
- New: /translationlist, /translationremove, /translationclear
- Legacy single-rule config auto-migrates on first edit
- 'off' mode with a source_channel removes only matching rules

PVE quests:
- Add 5 original themed progressive campaigns (44 quests total):
  * Ashes of Chernarus (8) - abandoned-research lab arc
  * The Drifter's Ledger (10) - moral-choice / merchant arc
  * Black Mountain Signal (8) - radio-tower mystery arc
  * Tide Watchers (8) - coastal lighthouse arc
  * Iron Convoy (10) - long-haul cargo / vehicle arc
- All quests share the 'Quest Line' kind so they auto-route to expeditions

PVE ticket flow:
- Every newly posted PVE quest embed now has a 'Submit Completion' button
- Clicking it auto-creates a private ticket channel under a
  '🎟️ PVE Quest Tickets' category, visible only to the player + admins
- On-interaction listener routes the button by custom_id, persistent
  across bot restarts (no per-quest View re-registration needed)
- Admins still approve via /pvecomplete inside the ticket
